### Resource page

For pages that map to a backend resource (organizations, members, roles, invitations, api-keys, billing):

```
src/pages/<resource>/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <RESOURCE>.OVERVIEW.md
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <resource>.route.tsx                   parent route ‚Äî renders the list
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <resource>.manifest.ts                     kind: 'layout', children: ['create', '$id', '$id-edit']
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <resource>.resource.ts                 resource manifest (endpoint, schema, permissions)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <resource>.contracts.ts                Zod ‚Äî shared across all CRUD views
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <resource>.api.ts                      optional; most resources use shared CRUD hooks
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <Resource>ListPage.tsx                 top-level UI ‚Äî the list
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/<Name>/{...}                list widgets (Table, Filters, EmptyState)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ forms/<Name>Form/{...}                 reusable forms consumed by dialogs
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ dialogs/<Name>Dialog/{...}             URL-driven action dialogs
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ hooks/use<Name>/{...}                  resource-specific hooks (most use shared CRUD)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ create/                                ‚Üí /<resource>/create   (renders null; list opens dialog)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ $<resource>Id/                         ‚Üí /<resource>/[id]     (show ‚Äî full-name $param folder)
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ edit/                              ‚Üí /<resource>/[id]/edit (renders null; list opens dialog)
```

Resource pages use `<Resource>ListPage.tsx` (PascalCase, page-prefixed) as the top-level UI. The list page mounts the action dialogs and reads URL to open them.

## CRUD UX convention ‚Äî URL-driven dialogs

For resource pages, the standard mapping:

| Action | URL | Renders | Why URL? |
|--------|-----|---------|----------|
| **List** | `/<resource>` | Page | Destination; must be shareable |
| **Create** | `/<resource>/create` | Dialog over list | Refresh-safe, deep-linkable |
| **Show** | `/<resource>/[id]` | Page or dialog over list | Shareable detail link |
| **Edit** | `/<resource>/[id]/edit` | Dialog over list | Refresh-safe, deep-linkable; `[id]` loads the row |
| **Delete** | *(no URL)* | Inline `AlertDialog` confirm | Transient one-click destructive action |
| **Quick toggles** | *(no URL)* | Inline button / dropdown | Transient |

On disk, `[id]` is a full-name `$param` folder ‚Äî `$memberId`, `$invoiceId` (never `$id`); its role files use the strip-`$` kebab prefix (`member-id.route.tsx`).

**Implementation pattern.** Parent `<Resource>ListPage.tsx` reads `useRouterState({ select: s => s.location.pathname })`, computes which dialog (if any) the URL implies, and renders it open. The list stays mounted behind the dialog backdrop.

**Forward compatibility ‚Äî promoting dialog ‚Üí full page.** When a Create/Edit dialog outgrows the modal (multi-step wizard, >15 fields, file uploads, shareable drafts):
1. URL stays the same (`/<resource>/create` or `/<resource>/[id]/edit`)
2. Replace the dialog mount in the list page with the sub-page's `route.tsx` rendering a full `<X>Page.tsx`
3. No URL break, no bookmark break

## Index redirects

When a layout has children, its index route (`/`) **redirects to the default child** via `beforeLoad`:

```ts
const indexRoute = createRoute({
  getParentRoute: () => parentRoute,
  path: '/',
  beforeLoad: () => { throw redirect({ to: '/parent/default-child' }); },
  component: () => null,
});
```

Established cases:
- `/` ‚Üí resolver route (last-used organization's dashboard, else `/organization`, else `/onboarding`)
- Future resource layouts with multiple children pick a default child

## Nested routes ‚Äî direct children (`<segment>/`, `$param/`)

When a page is `kind: 'layout'`, child routes nest **directly** as `<segment>/` ‚Äî the pages tree mirrors the URL tree 1:1; there is no `sub-pages/` bucket. Dynamic segments are `$param` folders with full-word param names (`$organizationSlug/`, `$patientId/`).

**`$param` naming rule (validator-enforced):** role files in a `$param` folder derive their prefix mechanically ‚Äî strip the `$`, kebab-case the rest: `$organizationSlug/` ‚Üí `organization-slug.route.tsx`, `organization-slug.manifest.ts`, `ORGANIZATION_SLUG.OVERVIEW.md`. Only the UI file stays human-named (`OrganizationLayout.tsx`, `PatientDetailPage.tsx`).

**Reserved segment names (validator-enforced):** `components`, `hooks`, `forms`, `dialogs`, `store`, `shared`, `__tests__` can never be route folders; `sub-pages` is retired. A `shared/` directory inside a layout page is the **family-shared** home (see Promotion ladder).

```
pages/organization/                       ‚Üí /organization (picker)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ organization.route.tsx
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ organization.manifest.ts                  kind: 'layout', children: ['$organizationSlug']
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ OrganizationPickerPage.tsx
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ $organizationSlug/                      ‚Üí /organization/$organizationSlug (org guard boundary)
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ organization-slug.route.tsx
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ organization-slug.manifest.ts         kind: 'layout', children: ['dashboard', 'suspended']
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ OrganizationLayout.tsx
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ dashboard/                        full island shape, recursively
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ suspended/
```

## Settings hash modal (and the `/` resolver)

Settings is **not a route space**. The global `SettingsModal` (`shared/components/SettingsModal/`) is mounted once on the root route and driven by the URL hash ‚Äî `#settings/<scope>/<section>` with scopes `account` | `organization` ‚Äî so it overlays ANY page (including deep organization URLs) without re-running route matching or unmounting the page behind it. Deep links reproduce page + modal, refresh keeps the section, back/Esc closes, and invalid hashes fall back to `#settings/account/profile`.

Route guards never see hashes: auth, organization-context, and permission gating live inside the modal (`settings-permissions.ts`, reusing `core/rbac` ‚Äî never forked). Open/section state lives in the URL hash ‚Äî never in `useUIStore` (the store is only for transient chrome: `sidebarOpen`, `commandPaletteOpen`). Hash changes are invisible to pageview analytics, so the modal emits an explicit PostHog event. Escape hatch: a section that becomes a heavy admin surface (members, billing, ‚Ä¶) is promoted to a real page under `pages/organization/$organizationSlug/`, keeping a hash ‚Üí path redirect shim.

`/` is the other folder-less URL: a pure resolver route (last-used organization's dashboard, else the `/organization` picker, else `/onboarding`) registered inline in `routeTree.tsx`.

## Dialog vs full page ‚Äî decision tree

When a sub-path exists under a page:

1. **Does it need a URL?**
   - YES ‚Üí either URL-driven dialog (sub-page renders null, parent shows dialog) or full page (sub-page renders Page UI)
   - NO ‚Üí local state (`useState` in parent's component)
2. **Page or dialog?**
   - **Page** when: complex, table-heavy, multi-step, mobile real estate matters, deep-link to detail context
   - **Dialog** when: form fits in modal, action stays in list context, transient
3. **Rule.** Everything between two `<page>.route.tsx` files belongs to the parent route's component.

## Promotion ladder (where code lives, by who uses it)

Everything starts **colocated** with its page. It climbs exactly one rung per force ‚Äî never higher:

```
used by‚Ä¶
  ONE page                                ‚Üí inside that page (components/, hooks/, <page>.api.ts, ‚Ä¶)
  the page + its OWN nested children      ‚Üí pages/<parent>/shared/        (family-shared)
  pages from DIFFERENT families,
  or any src/shared component             ‚Üí src/shared/                   (root shared)
  every layer / platform-level            ‚Üí src/core/ or src/lib/
```

**Family-shared (`pages/<parent>/shared/`)** ‚Äî for layout pages whose children share code:
- Same unit shapes as root shared: `shared/components/<X>/`, `shared/hooks/use<X>/`, plus plain family modules (`<name>-contracts.ts`, `<name>-api.ts`).
- Importable by the parent island and its descendants ONLY ‚Äî never by sibling families.
- Example: a chart widget used by `$organizationSlug/dashboard/` AND `$organizationSlug/reports/` ‚Üí `pages/organization/$organizationSlug/shared/components/<X>/` (NOT `src/shared/`).
- Note: the auth screens (`login/`, `mfa/`, ‚Ä¶) are top-level **siblings** (no parent island ‚Äî the `auth-shell` is pathless), so their shared code correctly lives in root `shared/api/auth-*` ‚Äî different families.

**Never promote when:**
- Only one page uses it (even if it looks "generic")
- It contains page-specific business logic

Promotion: move to the lowest rung that covers all consumers, update imports project-wide, delete the original ‚Äî never copy.

