`<name>-contracts.ts` modules: cohesion beats forcing a fake unit folder.

## Core Layer

The irreducible, app-state-free platform kernel ‚Äî one subfolder per domain:

```
src/core/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ config/                                 env schema, constants
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ data-provider/                          CRUD abstraction (HTTP REST adapter)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ http/                                   apiClient (fetch), interceptors, queryClient
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ rbac/                                   policies + guards (requireAuth, requirePermission)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ security/                               RBAC security gateway (gatewayFromManifest, gates)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ resources/                              resource registry (central manifest)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ types/                                  branded public-id types, permission codes
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ version/                                new-deployment detection
```

Auth runtime lives in `shared/auth/`, organization/tenancy runtime in `shared/tenancy/`,
errors in `shared/errors/`, and analytics/observability bootstrap in `app/` ‚Äî see
"Top-Level Layout" above for why each sits outside the kernel.

## State Management

| Scope | Library | Location |
|-------|---------|----------|
| Server state | TanStack Query | `pages/<page>/hooks/use<X>/` or `shared/hooks/use{List,One,Create,Update,Delete}/` |
| Global client state | Zustand | `src/shared/store/use<X>Store/` (incl. `useOrganizationStore` ‚Äî current tenant) |
| Page-local client state | Zustand | `src/pages/<page>/store/use<X>Store/` *(rare)* |
| Component-local | `useState` / `useReducer` | Inline; extract reducer to `<Component>.reducer.ts` when complex |
| Form state | react-hook-form + Zod | Inside the form component |
| URL state | TanStack Router | `<page>.search.ts` (validateSearch schema) |

**All Zustand stores live in `src/shared/store/<X>Store/`** (folder-per-unit) ‚Äî `useAuthStore`, `useOrganizationStore`, `useThemeStore`, `useUIStore`, `useOnboardingStore`, `useConsentStore`, `useLocaleStore`. There is no `core/<feature>/store.ts` pattern.

Cross-page API helpers (functions reused by both `pages/` and `shared/components/`) live in **`src/shared/api/`** (e.g., `shared/api/organization-api.ts`); organization/tenancy runtime lives in **`src/shared/tenancy/`** (e.g., `shared/tenancy/my-organizations.ts`).

Auth infrastructure (token storage, refresh timer, idle timeout, login/logout service) lives in **`src/shared/auth/`** ‚Äî not in core, because the HTTP client, error handler, shared components, and pages all need it.

**Rules:**
1. **Server state never goes in Zustand.** TanStack Query owns it.
2. **Page-local stores are an escape hatch** ‚Äî try `useState` ‚Üí `useReducer` ‚Üí URL search params ‚Üí shared store FIRST.
3. **Reducers live next to the component** that uses them. No `reducers/` directory.

## Tests

| Type | Location & file name |
|------|----------|
| Unit (component, hook, form, util, store) | Colocated `<Name>.test.{ts,tsx}` next to source |
| Full-stack UI + API (Playwright) | `tests/e2e/<name>.e2e.test.ts` or `<name>-api.e2e.test.ts` |

**`tests/e2e/`** ‚Äî all Playwright specs use **`*.e2e.test.ts`**. UI flows: `<name>.e2e.test.ts`; HTTP contracts: `<name>-api.e2e.test.ts`. Requires **core-be** on `:3000` (global-setup fails if down). Vitest excludes `tests/e2e`. Colocated unit tests keep plain `<Name>.test.{ts,tsx}`. Never use `.spec.ts`, or the words "real"/"live", in test file names.

**Strict test colocation (validator-enforced):** every component ‚Äî including each island's `<Page>Page.tsx`/`<Page>Layout.tsx` and the flat-group files in the `SettingsModal` tree ‚Äî and every hook ships a colocated `*.test.ts(x)`. `pnpm validate:structure` FAILS any unit folder, island top-level UI, or flat-group component without one. The only exemptions are the declarative role files below, barrels, and entry docs.

**No test file required for (the only exemptions):**
- `<page>.route.tsx` (thin wrapper)
- `<page>.manifest.ts` (declarative manifest)
- `<page>.contracts.ts` (Zod ‚Äî type-checked at compile, exercised where used)
- `<page>.search.ts`, `<page>.fixtures.ts`, `<page>.constants.ts` (declarative schemas / data)
- `<PAGE>.OVERVIEW.md`, `index.ts` (barrel re-exports)

## Import Rules

- Use `@/` alias for cross-layer imports from `src/`; within a page island use relative imports (`@/pages/**` is eslint-forbidden even from the same island)
- Always include `.ts`/`.tsx` extensions: `import { Button } from '@/shared/components/Button/index.ts'`
- Type-only imports: `import type { Org } from './<resource>.contracts.ts'`

**Dependency direction (one-way, with one documented exception):**

```
shared/components/ui ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ may import other ui primitives + lib
lib                  ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ may import from lib, core/types only
core                 ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ may import from lib, core/types (+ runtime trio, see below)
shared               ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ may import from core, lib, types
pages                ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ may import from shared, core, lib, types
app                  ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ may import from everything
```

**Runtime-trio exception (the only one):** the core kernel (`core/http`, `core/rbac`) may
import `shared/auth/`, `shared/errors/`, `useAuthStore`, and `useOrganizationStore`. Token
handling, error reporting, and permission checks are runtime services the kernel provides,
but that infrastructure is app-state- and SDK-dependent (Zustand, `@sentry/react`) so it
lives in `shared` (see Top-Level Layout). Core must never import any other `shared`
module. Enforced precisely by `no-restricted-imports` in `eslint.config.mjs`.

**Family-shared imports:** a page may import its ANCESTOR island's `shared/` (`pages/<parent>/shared/...`) ‚Äî that folder exists to be shared down the subtree. A parent's role files (`<parent>.api.ts`, ‚Ä¶) stay private to the parent; the explicit sharing surface is `shared/`.

**Never:**
- Page imports another page (`pages/A/` ‚Üõ `pages/B/`) ‚Äî including another family's `shared/`
- Shared imports from pages
- Core imports from pages, app, or any shared module outside the runtime trio
- UI primitives (`shared/components/ui/`) import anything internal except other ui primitives and `lib`

